n%20and%20ate%20a%20portion%20of%20it%20and%20then%20died%2C%26quot%3B%20The%20Times%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20argued%20in%20the%20deposition%20that%20he%20couldn't%20make%20as%20much%20money%20due%20to%20his%20health%2C%20and%20also%20revealed%20that%20he%20had%20mercury%20poisoning%20around%20the%20same%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKennedy%20has%20portrayed%20himself%20as%20the%20younger%2C%20more%20healthy%20alternative%20to%20the%20other%20two%20men%20running%20for%20president%2C%20Joe%20Biden%20and%20Donald%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%20campaign's%20press%20secretary%20confirmed%20that%20Kennedy%20was%20infected%20with%20a%20parasite%2010%20years%20ago%20and%20said%20it%20was%20resolved.%20His%20campaign%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Kennedy%20is%20in%20%26quot%3Brobust%20physical%20and%20mental%20health%26quot%3B%20and%20said%20questioning%20his%20fitness%20is%20a%20%26quot%3Bhilarious%20suggestion%2C%20given%20his%20competition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20could%20a%20parasitic%20worm%20even%20cause%20that%20kind%20of%20damage%3F%20One%20medical%20expert%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Kennedy's%20version%20of%20events%20doesn't%20quite%20add%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Janina%20Caira%2C%20a%20University%20of%20Connecticut%20professor%20and%20tapeworm%20specialist%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20Kennedy's%20parasite%20sounds%20more%20like%20the%20larvae%20of%20a%20pork%20tapeworm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20would%20be%20rare%2C%20Caira%20said%20in%20an%20email.%20Humans%20can%20be%20infected%20with%20the%20adult%20worm%20by%20eating%20undercooked%20pork%2C%20but%20can%20only%20be%20infected%20with%20the%20larvae%20after%20eating%20food%20or%20drinking%20water%20contaminated%20by%20the%20feces%20of%20someone%20with%20an%20adult%20tapeworm%20infection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20typically%20happens%20in%20areas%20with%20poor%20sanitation%2C%26quot%3B%20Caira%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20he%20could%20have%20contracted%20the%20infection%20in%20South%20Asia%20if%20he%20came%20into%20contact%20with%20food%20or%20water%20contaminated%20with%20eggs%20of%20the%20tapeworm.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there's%20no%20way%20the%20larvae%20could%20have%20consumed%20Kennedy's%20brain%20tissue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAbsolutely%20not%2C%26quot%3B%20Caira%20wrote.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20said%20the%20larvae%20don't%20have%20mouths%20or%20digestive%20systems.%20Instead%2C%20they%20absorb%20nutrients%20through%20the%20surface%20of%20their%20bodies.%20While%20Caira%20said%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20a%20worm%20could%20do%20some%20%26quot%3Bmechanical%20damage%26quot%3B%20to%20nearby%20brain%20tissue%2C%20the%20larvae%20are%20very%20small%2C%20and%20a%20single%20one%20%26quot%3Bwould%20not%20cause%20much%20damage.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20lines%20up%20with%20what%20experts%2C%20who%20were%20skeptical%20of%20the%20details%2C%20told%20The%20New%20York%20Times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Dr.%20Peter%20Hotez%2C%20a%20pediatrician%20and%20global%20health%20advocate%20who%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20pediatrics%20and%20molecular%20virology%20%26amp%3B%20microbiology%20at%20Baylor%20College%20of%20Medicine%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FPeterHotez%2Fstatus%2F1788207477441348075%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewrote%20on%20X%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Bneuroparasitic%20diseases%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bparasitic%20worms%20have%20a%20huge%20impact%20on%20the%20human%20brain.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHotez%20said%20the%20diseases%20are%20seen%20in%20poor%20populations%2C%20with%20a%20%26quot%3Bsurprising%20amount%20of%20illness%26quot%3B%20in%20southern%20states%20and%20Texas.%20He%20said%20his%20team%20at%20the%20National%20School%20of%20Tropical%20Medicine%20is%20working%20on%20low-cost%20vaccines%20to%20prevent%20the%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frfk