Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20Force%20veteran%20Terens%20will%20be%20honored%20on%20June%206%20at%20a%20commemoration%20of%20the%2080th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20D-Day%20landings%20in%20Normandy%2C%20the%20historic%20Allied%20operation%20that%20changed%20the%20course%20of%20the%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20later%20Harold%20and%20Jeanne%20will%20exchange%20vows%20in%20Carentan-les-Marais%2C%20close%20to%20the%20beaches%20where%20thousands%20of%20soldiers%20waded%20ashore%20--%20and%20many%20died%20--%20that%20day%20in%201944.%20The%20town's%20mayor%20will%20preside%20over%20the%20ceremony.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20love%20story%20like%20you've%20never%20heard%20before%2C%26quot%3B%20Terens%20assures%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20an%20interview%20at%20Swerlin's%20home%20in%20Boca%20Raton%2C%20Florida%2C%20they%20exchange%20glances%2C%20hold%20hands%20and%20smooch%20like%20teenagers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHe's%20an%20unbelievable%20guy%2C%20I%20love%20everything%20about%20him%2C%26quot%3B%20Swerlin%20says%20of%20her%20fiance.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20handsome%20--%20and%20he's%20a%20good%20kisser.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20youthful%20centenarian%20is%20also%20cheerful%2C%20witty%2C%20and%20gifted%20with%20a%20prodigious%20and%20vivid%20memory%2C%20recalling%20dates%20and%20locations%20and%20events%20without%20hesitation%20--%20a%20living%20history%20book%20of%20sorts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShortly%20after%20Terens%20turned%2018%2C%20Japan%20bombed%20the%20US%20Navy%20base%20at%20Pearl%20Harbor.%20He%2C%20like%20many%20young%20American%20men%2C%20was%20keen%20to%20enlist.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20age%2020%20he%20was%20an%20expert%20in%20Morse%20code%20and%20aboard%20a%20ship%20bound%20for%20England%2C%20where%20he%20was%20assigned%20to%20a%20squadron%20of%20four%20P-47%20Thunderbolt%20fighters.%20Terens%20was%20responsible%20for%20their%20ground-to-air%20communication.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20losing%20the%20war%20by%20losing%20a%20lot%20of%20planes%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20pilots...%20These%20pilots%20became%20friends%20and%20they%20got%20killed%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20laments.%20%26quot%3BThey%20were%20all%20young%20kids.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20company%20lost%20half%20of%20its%2060%20planes%20during%20the%20Normandy%20operation.%20Soon%20after%2C%20Terens%20volunteered%20to%20travel%20to%20that%20region%20of%20northern%20France%20to%20help%20transport%20German%20prisoners%20of%20war%20and%20liberated%20Allied%20troops%20to%20England.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E-%20Secret%20mission%20-%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20day%20Terens%20received%20an%20envelope%20with%20instructions%20not%20to%20open%20it%20until%20he%20reached%20a%20certain%20destination.%20Thus%20began%20a%20remarkable%20journey%20that%20took%20him%20to%20Soviet%20Ukraine%20via%20Casablanca%2C%20Algeria%2C%20Tunisia%2C%20Libya%2C%20Cairo%2C%20Baghdad%20and%20Tehran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20he%20finally%20arrived%20in%20Poltava%2C%20a%20city%20east%20of%20Kyiv%2C%20a%20Russian%20officer%20informed%20him%20he%20was%20part%20of%20a%20secret%20mission.%20US%20B-17%20aircraft%20were%20taking%20off%20from%20England%20bound%20for%20Romania%2C%20where%20they%20would%20bomb%20Axis%20oil%20fields%20controlled%20by%20Nazi%20Germany.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETerens%20was%20part%20of%20the%20resupply%20team%20in%20Ukraine%20that%20provided%20the%20Flying%20Fortresses%20with%20fuel%20and%20ordnance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20operation%20lasted%2024%20hours%20until%20the%20Germans%20discovered%20the%20Allied%20base%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20attacked%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETerens%20says%20he%20escaped%20but%20was%20left%20in%20no-man's%20land.%20He%20contracted%20dysentery%2C%20and%20only%20survived%20thanks%20to%20the%20help%20of%20a%20local%20farming%20family.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReturning%20to%20England%2C%20he%20cheated%20death%20once%20more.%20When%20a%20pub%20proprietor%20refused%20to%20serve%20him%20a%20drink%20because%20she%20was%20about%20to%20close%2C%20he%20shrugged%20and%20left.%20He%20had%20barely%20walked%20two%20blocks%20when%20a%20German%20rocket%20destroyed%20the%20establishment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Luckiest%20guy%20in%20the%20world'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20war%20he%20returned%20stateside%20and%20married%20Thelma%2C%20his%20wife%20of%2070%20years%20with%20whom%20he%20raised%20three%20children.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETerens%20worked%20for%20a%20British%20multinational%2C%20and%20when%20he%20and%20Thelma%20retired%2C%20they%20settled%20in%20Florida.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20death%20in%202018%20sank%20Terens%2C%20and%20he%20endured%20%26quot%3Bthree%20years%20of%20feeling%20sorry%20for%20myself%20and%20mourning%20my%20wife%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20life%20offered%20him%20a%20fresh%20start.%20In%202021%20a%20friend%20introduced%20him%20to%20Jeanne%20Swerlin%2C%20a%20charismatic%20woman%20who%20had%20also%20been%20widowed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESparks%20did%20not%20fly.%20On%20their%20first%20meeting%20Terens%20could%20barely%20look%20at%20Swerlin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20persistence%20paid%20off.%20A%20second%20date%20changed%20everything%2C%20and%20they%20haven't%20been%20apart%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20lights%20up%20my%20life%2C%20she%20makes%20everything%20beautiful%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20says.%20%26quot%3BShe%20makes%20life%20worth%20living.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETerens%2C%20wearing%20a%20World%20War%20II%20cap%20with%20%26quot%3B100%20Year%20Old%20Vet%26quot%3B%20embroidered%20on%20the%20side%2C%20is%20over%20the%20moon%20about%20returning%20to%20France%2C%20where%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20bestowed%20on%20him%20the%20nation's%20highest%20distinction%2C%20the%20Legion%20of%20Honor%2C%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20also%20thrilled%2C%20of%20course%2C%20about%20getting%20married.%20Surrounded%20by%20family%20and%20friends%2C%20December%20lovebirds%20Jeanne%20and%20Harold%20will%2